    narr:generatedFrom "c354f003fe2a54a8d5d3268a64e6f8923cccb163" ;
    narr:narration """This hub collects observations about antithesis as both a rhetorical device and a structural organizing principle across the aswritten corpus, spanning style memos from mid-2025 through July 2026. The dominant pattern is [antithesis-as-document-spine](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisStructure): entire documents are organized as series of binary contrast pairs that resolve into design decisions — [decay vs. depreciation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AgentSim_Antithesis), [conviction vs. temporality](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisConvictionTemporality), [sponsor vs. champion](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_Antithesis_SponsorChampion), [trial vs. payment](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisTrialVsPayment). A recurring sub-pattern is the [before/after rename antithesis](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisBeforeAfter_Distillation) and the [rejected-path-named-first idiom](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_WriteFlow_AntithesisStructure). By June 2026, a prescriptive rule emerged: [the 'X, not Y' sentence-closing form is explicitly prohibited](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_NoXNotYAntithesis) as momentum-killing, with the injunction to rebuild contrast through belief-specifics-belief instead. Some antitheses carry the argument structurally — [the rhetorical structure IS the design heuristic](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_MCPSession_KeyAxisAntithesis) — while others function as [aphoristic compression](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_IntelligenceVsPerspective) or [three-beat reframes](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisRhetoric). The [three-axis antithesis against AGI](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_SII_ThreeAxisAntithesis) represents the device at maximum compression. Coverage spans product strategy, architecture, fundraising, sales, and system design.""" ;
